column1: #Text=Michał z Wrocławia , Michał Wrocławczyk , Michael de Wratislava , Michael Vratislaviensis ( ca . 1450 or 1460 in Wrocław – 1534 ) was a Polish [ 2 ] Scholastic philosopher , astronomer , astrologer , mathematician , theologian , philologist , and professor of the Kraków Academy . [ 3 ]
#Text=Michał Falkener was born in Silesia to a family of wealthy burghers .

#Text=In Latin — the language favored by medieval European scholars , and used in his works — he is sometimes referred to as " Vratislaviensis " [ 4 ] or " Wratislaviensis " ( " the Wrocławian " ) in addition to " Michaelis de Vratislauia " [ 5 ] ( " Michael of Wrocław " ) .
